{"TopicId":218847,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"Can\u0026#039;t upload images directly anymore","CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-11T10:52:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-11T10:52:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t see any forum technical support, so I\u0027m posting here...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUp until one week ago, I could upload an image on imgur, then right-click copy it, and paste it on the forum. The forum would recognize this as meaning it must take the image url.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow, it does not work anymore, It says I cannot post images directly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I have to click \u0022insert image from url\u0022, copy the url, and add .png. Which is a lot more annoying when I have to post dozens of pictures.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat changed there? is there some way to get back the easy uploading?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-11T17:11:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTest.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p5efD.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/p5efD.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe method I have always used is copy/pasting the BBCode link from Imgur straight into my posts without any formatting.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, also, your question has been moved to Kerbal Network.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-11T19:18:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t right click \u0022copy image\u0022, I\u0027d do \u0022Copy link to image\u0022 instead. That should paste the direct link that ends with jpg/png/gif/potato/whatever and forum software should transform it in