eatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-12T16:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224311401\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218847\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221691856164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nah, it works.\u003Cbr\u003E\ni was using \u0022copy link\u0022 from imgur. there was a big button for it, it seemed the right thing to do. the option on the right click of the mouse works properly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand my screenshots are in png format\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t matter what you upload to imgur, you can link to a jpg and it\u0027ll give a jpg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit\u0027s in their best interest to spend the time re-encoding the file, as it lowers the bandwidth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-13T14:34:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224311407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022218847\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221691858042\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit\u0027s in their best interest to spend the time re-encoding the file, as it lowers the bandwidth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpon quick inspection it doesn\u0027t matter. I tried png, switching to jpg and even gif. All three files downloaded with the same size.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}